Related Transactions with Nippon Cable System Inc. Group 
         Most of the transactions were sales and purchase of supplies and products between the Company and the 
companies within Nippon Cable System Inc. Group.  The main reason why the Company had to sell and/or purchase
products with these companies is that each company in this group has a policy of controlling its manufacturing costs. 
It is, therefore, customary for companies within Nippon Cable System Inc Group to source high quality raw materials
and component parts from other companies - both within and outside Nippon Cable System Inc. Group - if it is more
economical than manufacturing them themselves.   Hence, there are some occasions that the sourcing may be from 
other companies within the group.  In addition, each company may also source raw materials and component parts 
in the event that it cannot manufacture enough to meet customer's order.  In summary, related transactions between 
the Company and companies within Nippon Cable System Inc. Group are primarily for the purpose of supporting 
high quality component parts at competitive price to other companies within the group.

