Scope of Duties and Responsibilities
         1.  Review financial statement preparation process to ensure accuracy and adequacy
         2.  Review internal control system and internal audit system to ensure suitability and effectiveness
         3.  Review the above processes to ensure compliance with Securities and Stock Exchange laws and regulations, 
SET Notifications or other laws related to the Company's business
         4.  Consider, select and nominate auditor and propose auditor's compensation
         5.  Ensure accurate and complete disclosure of connected transactions or transactions with possible conflict 
of interests
         6.   Prepare Corporate Governance report to be included in the Company's Annual Report.  Such report must 
be signed by the Chairman of the Audit Committee
         7.  Perform other duties as assigned by the Board of Directors and agreed by the Audit Committee

Terms for Holding Office
         1.  Chairman    3 Years
         2.   Member     3 Years

