Silent Period   
         Shareholders, who own common shares before the Company's public offering, holding 201,500,000 
shares or 100% of paid-up capital before the initial public offering certify to the Stock Exchange of Thailand 
that their shares will not be sold for the period of one and a half years from the trading date.  Upon the expiry 
of each 6 months period of the prescribed time, those shareholders will be allowed to sell of 25% of the total 
amount of shares prohibited for sale and the rest after one and a half years.

